post_text:
Registration for High School students has gone extremely well this week. A special thank you and kudos to our new Counselor Cory Neal. He, along with Karma and Mrs. Paulson were instrumental in everything running so smoothly.

Next week all K through 8th grade students will be registering on Tuesday and Wednesday from 9:00 to 4:00. Please sign up online for an appointment. Any high school students who were unable to sign up this week can come in during the morning from 9:00 to 12:00 on those days.

Finally, and very importantly, if you are contemplating choosing online schooling, we need to know by the end of the day on Wednesday, August 12th.

Thank you,
Mark Shore, Principal

post_text: Good afternoon everyone. Yesterday Governor Parson in collaboration with the DESE ordered all Missouri Public schools to shut down for the remainder of the school year. Districts are required to continue to provide distance learning during this time through the remainder of the school year. For us this is May 13th. We will provide additional information on how our District will respond to this order moving forward but wanted you to be aware of this recent development. Within a half hour of the announcement MSHSAA announced the cancellation of all remaining postseason events for the 2019-2020 school year. We know this is an announcement that saddens everyone. There will be a school board meeting April 15th that will address the questions we all have about Prom, Graduation of not just the Seniors, but Eighth Grade, and Kindergarten. Hopefully answers will be found.

post_text: Panthers, I want to clear up a quick rumor that has grown legs and started to run wild on Facebook and other places. We have not - I repeat NOT (N-O-T) - cancelled the choir program or anything like that. If you are confused about your child’s schedule or have questions, please feel free to contact me directly (dheeb@prairiehome.k12.mo.us). I would be glad to help.
